WEBVTT

01:30.676 --> 01:32.575
[BIRD CAWING]

01:46.209 --> 01:49.626
[]

01:49.764 --> 01:52.664
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

01:58.325 --> 01:59.602
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

02:07.506 --> 02:08.645
[GASPS]

02:21.555 --> 02:24.558
Got to move! Get the kids!
We gotta get home!

02:26.353 --> 02:28.009
Crazy woman.

02:41.471 --> 02:44.336
[]

03:14.711 --> 03:16.230
[ELEVATOR DOOR DINGS]

03:17.783 --> 03:19.509
[SIGHS]

03:30.037 --> 03:32.488
Ah, speak of the devil.
How'd it go?Great.

03:32.626 --> 03:35.042
Did you get your source?Absolutely.

03:35.180 --> 03:36.077
Good.

03:38.287 --> 03:41.773
Dana, we're gonna put Rosenblum
on your story.

03:41.911 --> 03:44.293
Excuse me?You're short on manpower.

03:44.431 --> 03:46.226
And you know I hate
losing to the Post.

03:46.364 --> 03:47.710
We're not gonna lose
to the Post.

03:47.848 --> 03:49.229
Don't get me started
on the Journal.

03:49.367 --> 03:50.816
We're not gonna lose
to the Journal.

03:50.954 --> 03:52.577
Especially not
with my help.

03:52.715 --> 03:55.856
What are you gonna do?I got Sandberg.

03:55.994 --> 03:57.858
You actually talked to him?

03:57.996 --> 04:00.723
We're sitting down next week.When?

04:00.861 --> 04:03.208
[STAMMERS]

04:03.346 --> 04:07.799
I wanna hear everything you got
by Monday's page-one meeting.

04:07.937 --> 04:11.181
Meantime,
you two exchange notes.

04:11.320 --> 04:13.667
When next week?It's not set yet.

04:13.805 --> 04:15.841
Oh. Okay, so all of this
is predicated

04:15.979 --> 04:18.188
on a meeting
you don't actually have.

04:18.327 --> 04:20.536
No, no, I said it's not set
yet, but next week.

04:20.674 --> 04:23.366
No, you said it wasn't set yet.No, I said it's not set, until--

04:23.504 --> 04:25.437
Are you for real?No. Yes.

04:25.575 --> 04:27.370
Uh, Dana?He just says "Sandberg,"

04:27.508 --> 04:29.165
and suddenly he's on my story?Dana.

04:29.303 --> 04:30.615
Because I've come to you
a thousand times

04:30.753 --> 04:33.652
and it's never been that easy.Yeah.

04:33.790 --> 04:36.137
When you sit down with him,
tell him I said hi.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.829
Dana.Because I just had that meeting

04:37.967 --> 04:40.072
that you think you're gonna get.Dana. Dana.

04:40.210 --> 04:41.142
What?

04:47.390 --> 04:48.426
Shit.

04:55.364 --> 04:57.469
Hang on a minute.It's me.

04:57.607 --> 04:59.437
I heard what happened.

04:59.575 --> 05:02.302
Rosenblum is telling everybody
he's on your story now.

05:02.440 --> 05:05.477
Oh, I can't stand
his little smug ass.

05:05.615 --> 05:08.515
Why you still breastfeeding?
Jordan's 1.

05:08.653 --> 05:10.793
Because the World Health
Organization recommends it

05:10.931 --> 05:12.622
for up to two years and beyond.

05:12.760 --> 05:14.900
Kid's got a mouth
full of teeth, D.

05:15.038 --> 05:17.731
He's gonna be able to spell
"milk" pretty soon.

05:17.869 --> 05:19.042
Doesn't it hurt?

05:19.180 --> 05:21.217
It's a good way
for us to stay close.

05:24.496 --> 05:26.912
How you doing?My blouse is almost dry.

05:27.050 --> 05:28.880
I'm not asking
about your blouse.

05:30.399 --> 05:31.779
Please don't isolate yourself.

05:31.917 --> 05:33.712
I'm not isolated,
we're talking right now.

05:33.850 --> 05:36.059
You know what I mean, D.
You work, you go home.

05:36.197 --> 05:38.545
That's all you ever do.I'm a single mother.

05:40.305 --> 05:43.343
All right.
You're not gonna talk to me,

05:43.481 --> 05:45.345
you better talk to someone.I am fine.

05:45.483 --> 05:46.932
I don't think you're fine.

05:47.070 --> 05:48.520
I would tell you if I wasn't.

05:49.797 --> 05:52.282
Now, if you will excuse me,

05:52.421 --> 05:55.700
I have to go make sure little
Rosenblum stays off my story.

06:10.715 --> 06:13.234
How you doing, Manny?Evening, Ms. Canedy.

06:13.373 --> 06:15.961
Saw little man earlier.
Not so little anymore.

06:16.099 --> 06:17.929
Who are you telling?[CHUCKLES]

06:21.415 --> 06:23.797
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

06:23.935 --> 06:26.040
How is he?Taking his nap.

06:26.178 --> 06:27.732
Still?

06:27.870 --> 06:29.768
Hope he's not coming down
with something.

06:29.906 --> 06:34.014
No. No, that boy ran wild
in the park.

06:34.152 --> 06:37.569
I had to pry him away.Thank you, Kaleisha.

06:37.707 --> 06:40.020
You should go on home.Okay, let me finish up,

06:40.158 --> 06:42.332
and I'll see you tomorrow,
all right?
Okay.

06:54.241 --> 06:57.140
[]

07:33.522 --> 07:35.455
[SHOES CLATTER]

07:38.009 --> 07:39.700
[GROANS SOFTLY]

07:59.996 --> 08:01.860
[BABY CRYING]

08:04.345 --> 08:05.657
Here I come.

08:21.190 --> 08:22.985
Tell him everything, Ma.

08:23.123 --> 08:25.021
[GASPS, PANTING]

09:34.919 --> 09:37.197
"Dear Jordan,

09:37.335 --> 09:40.580
I want you to know that it's
all right for boys to cry.

09:42.823 --> 09:47.794
Sometimes crying can release
a lot of pain and stress.

10:01.601 --> 10:04.776
It has nothing to do
with your manhood."

10:08.815 --> 10:10.333
Your father wrote that.

10:13.923 --> 10:17.444
He wrote this whole thing.
Just for you.

10:21.172 --> 10:23.933
I thought you should hear it
because...

10:24.071 --> 10:27.937
[BREATHES DEEPLY]
...well, you cry a lot.

10:36.463 --> 10:39.397
Dear Jordan,
if you are reading this

10:39.535 --> 10:43.366
it means that we got through
the sorrowful years somehow,

10:43.504 --> 10:45.575
and that you are old enough
to understand

10:45.714 --> 10:47.681
all that I am
about to tell you.

10:58.519 --> 11:04.249
The first time I saw your
father, Charles Monroe King,

11:04.387 --> 11:07.563
was in the living room
of the house where I grew up.

11:07.701 --> 11:10.186
It was the spring of 1998.

11:10.324 --> 11:12.568
And I was visiting your
grandfather for this birthday.

11:12.706 --> 11:15.433
[LISA STANSFIELD'S
"ALL AROUND THE WORLD"
PLAYING ON RADIO]

11:15.571 --> 11:18.022
DANA [SINGING ALONG]:

12:08.797 --> 12:10.419
So, baby, how's Dwayne doing?

12:10.557 --> 12:13.111
Mike, come on.Mama, I told you, we broke up.

12:13.249 --> 12:15.700
Well, flames rekindle.
Look at your brother.

12:15.838 --> 12:17.633
Remember when he
and Charlene fell out?

12:17.771 --> 12:19.635
Yeah. I'm shocked
she took him back.

12:19.773 --> 12:22.258
Well, you never know.
Did you call him?

12:22.396 --> 12:23.915
Now, why would I do that?

12:24.053 --> 12:26.642
You're the one who said
he's so perfect.
Mommy.

12:26.780 --> 12:28.437
Works on Wall Street.Ma.

12:28.575 --> 12:29.783
Ivy League.I know.

12:29.921 --> 12:31.060
Speaks Italian.

12:31.198 --> 12:32.786
We are not getting back
together, okay?

12:32.924 --> 12:34.443
It's over.You never know.

12:34.581 --> 12:37.722
No, Mom.
Some things you do know.

12:37.860 --> 12:38.965
Well, well, well.

12:39.103 --> 12:42.969
[CHUCKLES]Oops. Sorry.

12:53.289 --> 12:54.981
[SIGHS]

12:58.639 --> 12:59.537
Grace?

13:02.747 --> 13:04.507
Bless us, oh, Lord,

13:04.645 --> 13:07.994
for these gifts we're about
to receive from thy bounty

13:08.132 --> 13:10.513
through Christ our Lord. Amen.

13:10.651 --> 13:11.514
Amen.Amen.

13:11.652 --> 13:12.584
Amen.

13:23.009 --> 13:24.355
Who's smoking reefer
out here?

13:24.493 --> 13:26.012
[COUGHING]
Shit.[LAUGHS]

13:26.150 --> 13:28.531
Y'all know this house
is downwind, right?

13:28.669 --> 13:30.671
You want a hit?You know I don't smoke.

13:30.810 --> 13:32.639
You can't think
when you're high.

13:32.777 --> 13:35.642
Might help you relax.I'm relaxed.

13:35.780 --> 13:37.955
You think
I need to relax?

13:38.093 --> 13:40.820
What? Do you?Girl, yes.

13:40.958 --> 13:43.926
Okay, maybe I'm a little type A.A little?

13:44.064 --> 13:45.376
[COUGHING]

13:45.514 --> 13:47.412
They stress me out.

13:47.550 --> 13:49.690
Why you think
I'm staying at a hotel?

13:49.829 --> 13:52.797
Same reason we out here
getting high.

13:52.935 --> 13:55.904
I just don't understand how she
stays with him all these years.

13:56.042 --> 13:59.562
She loves him.That is not love. It's fear.

13:59.700 --> 14:01.771
She's scared
to end up alone.

14:01.910 --> 14:04.153
Is that how it is, Mike?

14:04.291 --> 14:06.052
Huh?

14:06.190 --> 14:08.882
Is that how it is
being married?

14:09.020 --> 14:10.263
Is what how it is?

14:10.401 --> 14:11.816
[BOTH LAUGH]

14:11.954 --> 14:14.750
Aren't you scared
you're gonna end up alone?

14:14.888 --> 14:16.200
No, not really.

14:16.338 --> 14:18.858
Shit, sometimes I wish
she would leave me alone.

14:20.066 --> 14:23.517
But are you happy?Yeah.

14:23.655 --> 14:27.038
We fight and shit, but yeah.See, there's hope.

14:27.176 --> 14:29.316
Now I just gotta find
the right guy.

14:29.454 --> 14:31.008
Good luck.

14:31.146 --> 14:33.493
Men are luxuries.
Not necessities.

14:33.631 --> 14:34.666
Damn.Damn.

14:34.804 --> 14:35.909
I'm not playing.

14:36.047 --> 14:37.359
Apparently not.

14:37.497 --> 14:38.567
[ALL LAUGH]

14:38.705 --> 14:39.706
It's cold,
I'll see y'all inside.

14:39.844 --> 14:40.880
All right.

15:01.693 --> 15:04.351
Hi.Hi.

15:04.489 --> 15:06.146
I'm a friend of your father's.

15:06.284 --> 15:08.493
Oh.[CHUCKLES]

15:08.631 --> 15:11.911
Are you Dana or Gwen?Dana.

15:13.050 --> 15:15.086
The journalist.

15:15.224 --> 15:16.916
And you are?

15:17.054 --> 15:20.954
Oh. I'm, uh, First Sergeant
Charles King, at your service.

15:21.092 --> 15:23.681
Oh. You're a soldier.Yes, ma'am.

15:23.819 --> 15:26.132
Your father was my drill
sergeant back in the day.

15:28.444 --> 15:30.722
I just came by
to hang this for him.

15:30.860 --> 15:33.346
Early birthday present.

15:33.484 --> 15:35.865
761st Tank Battalion.

15:36.004 --> 15:38.765
Some of the bravest men
to fight in World War II.

15:38.903 --> 15:41.941
Me and your dad are tankers,
so we share a mutual admiration.

15:43.597 --> 15:45.082
What do you think about it?

15:47.981 --> 15:49.293
It's beautiful.

15:50.535 --> 15:52.813
Is that pointillism?

15:52.952 --> 15:54.677
Yes, ma'am, it is.

15:54.815 --> 15:56.576
You know, like Georges Seurat.

15:56.714 --> 15:59.544
Takes a bit more time,
but I think it's worth it.

16:00.960 --> 16:04.653
You drew that?Yes, ma'am.

16:04.791 --> 16:07.242
[SOFTLY]
Technically,
it's a painting.

16:07.380 --> 16:10.176
[NORMALLY]
But I won't hold it against you.

16:10.314 --> 16:14.042
You know, sarge talks
about you a lot.

16:14.180 --> 16:18.011
Does he?Nonstop. All three of you.

16:18.149 --> 16:20.393
You're his pride and joy.

16:20.531 --> 16:23.499
Is he here?Yes, ma'am.

16:23.637 --> 16:25.156
He's out on the porch.

16:25.294 --> 16:28.470
I told him to wait there
while I finished hanging this.

16:28.608 --> 16:30.196
Excuse me real quick.

16:36.512 --> 16:39.722
Morning, Daddy.Oh, good morning.

16:39.860 --> 16:42.380
Happy birthday.Oh...

16:42.518 --> 16:44.969
I know it's not till tomorrow,
but these are cigars,

16:45.107 --> 16:46.798
so don't let Mommy see them.

16:46.936 --> 16:48.317
Thank you, pumpkin.

16:48.455 --> 16:50.009
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

16:53.357 --> 16:56.705
So your friend in there.

16:56.843 --> 16:58.638
He finish putting
my picture up yet?

16:58.776 --> 17:00.778
Not yet.
But you're gonna love it.

17:03.022 --> 17:06.404
He's, uh, talented, isn't he?
And good looking.

17:09.338 --> 17:10.546
Did Gwen meet him yet?

17:10.684 --> 17:13.101
No, she's been out
with your mom all morning.

17:14.378 --> 17:15.586
Oh...

17:17.381 --> 17:19.659
Just tell him you forgot
something at your hotel,

17:19.797 --> 17:21.040
your sister
wants to borrow your car.

17:21.178 --> 17:23.042
Daddy.I'm just trying to help.

17:23.180 --> 17:24.491
Don't.

17:24.629 --> 17:25.872
Okay.

17:28.875 --> 17:29.772
[SIGHS]

17:39.403 --> 17:42.613
Excuse me? Hi.

17:42.751 --> 17:44.132
Can I ask you a favor?

17:44.270 --> 17:46.272
I left my cell phone
back at my hotel,

17:46.410 --> 17:49.033
and my sister needs to borrow
my car when she gets back.

17:49.171 --> 17:51.277
Would you mind
giving me a ride?

18:02.322 --> 18:04.083
You mind if I
turn on the radio?

18:04.221 --> 18:06.533
No, sure.

18:06.671 --> 18:08.949
What kind of music
do you like?

18:09.088 --> 18:10.779
There should be
a CD in there.

18:10.917 --> 18:14.023
[THE SPINNERS' "SADIE" PLAYING]

18:16.440 --> 18:19.339
Oldies?Yeah, that's the Spinners.

18:27.451 --> 18:30.937
You don't talk much, do you?Yeah, I do.

18:31.075 --> 18:33.595
I mean,
when I got something to say.

18:33.733 --> 18:34.665
Okay.

18:38.013 --> 18:40.326
So my dad
was your drill sergeant?

18:40.464 --> 18:41.706
Yes, ma'am.

18:41.844 --> 18:44.019
He taught me
how to be a soldier.

18:44.157 --> 18:47.436
I'm lucky I met him.
Both of your folks.

18:48.610 --> 18:50.025
They've been there for me.

18:52.165 --> 18:53.442
Good.

19:11.011 --> 19:12.668
[HONKING]Go! You want an invite?

19:14.670 --> 19:15.706
Sorry.

19:18.364 --> 19:21.125
You can take the girl
out of the city...

19:21.263 --> 19:23.576
you can't take the city
out of the girl.

19:35.795 --> 19:39.385
You know I'm a journalist,
so I have to ask.

19:39.523 --> 19:42.146
My parents have been there
for you how?

19:47.358 --> 19:49.257
I'm going through a divorce.

19:49.395 --> 19:51.017
Oh.

19:52.743 --> 19:55.090
I'm sorry.Eh, don't be.

19:56.850 --> 19:58.749
[SIGHS]

19:58.887 --> 20:00.751
Your mom's a great listener,

20:00.889 --> 20:03.788
and Pop always invites me over
to watch ball games.

20:03.926 --> 20:06.619
Pop?Yes, ma'am.

20:06.757 --> 20:09.104
I mean, don't get me wrong,
I love my parents,

20:09.242 --> 20:13.384
but I don't think I would have
made it through without yours.

20:13.522 --> 20:15.421
Hmm.

20:15.559 --> 20:17.492
Why do you seem
so surprised?

20:17.630 --> 20:19.114
You didn't grow up with them.

20:21.944 --> 20:24.809
What about you?What about me?

20:27.398 --> 20:29.400
You seeing someone?

20:29.538 --> 20:31.402
I'm surprised my parents
didn't tell you

20:31.540 --> 20:33.749
since you all talk so much.

20:36.890 --> 20:39.272
I'm single. Recently.

20:43.552 --> 20:45.968
Hey, listen, I'm supposed to go
to the house tomorrow

20:46.106 --> 20:47.936
for the barbeque.

20:48.074 --> 20:50.421
I could pick you up
on my way if you want.

20:52.872 --> 20:55.909
Yeah, that'd be great.

20:56.047 --> 20:59.119
How's 0900?

20:59.258 --> 21:00.500
Early.

21:03.089 --> 21:04.332
That's perfect.

21:05.609 --> 21:07.473
[SNORING]

21:09.060 --> 21:11.684
[KNOCKING]

21:11.822 --> 21:15.550
No housekeeping.
Come back later.

21:15.688 --> 21:17.517
It's Charles King.

21:17.655 --> 21:19.830
Who?

21:19.968 --> 21:22.281
First Sergeant Charles King.Oh, shit.

21:22.419 --> 21:24.662
Uh, what-what time is it?

21:24.800 --> 21:27.389
Uh,49.

21:27.527 --> 21:29.564
I asked for a wake-up call,
I'm so sorry.

21:29.702 --> 21:31.428
Don't worry about it.

21:35.742 --> 21:37.296
I'll be right out.

21:37.434 --> 21:39.643
I-it's okay. Take your time.

21:39.781 --> 21:42.266
I won't be long. Sh--!
I promise.

21:42.404 --> 21:44.095
Whenever you're ready,
I'll be here.

21:44.233 --> 21:45.442
Shit! Shit!

22:01.527 --> 22:05.393
I'm so sorry.It was worth the wait.

22:11.744 --> 22:13.573
Um, hi.Hi.

22:14.885 --> 22:18.267
Are you hungry?I could eat.

22:18.406 --> 22:19.752
All right. After you.

22:28.070 --> 22:29.900
So, what made you join the Army?

22:31.764 --> 22:34.525
The discipline.
The travel.

22:34.663 --> 22:38.115
And I love my country,
so I always wanted to serve.

22:38.253 --> 22:40.635
Plus, the camo
just brings out my eyes.

22:42.464 --> 22:44.708
It's a tough way
to make a living.

22:44.846 --> 22:45.916
Yes, ma'am, it is.

22:47.400 --> 22:49.057
You know you don't
have to call me ma'am.

22:49.195 --> 22:51.473
I know. I don't want to either.

22:54.062 --> 22:55.960
Belgian waffle.
Side of hash browns.

22:56.098 --> 22:57.928
Thank you.And...

22:58.066 --> 23:00.482
I've got scrambled
egg whites and oatmeal.

23:00.620 --> 23:02.864
Perfect.
Got you a little
extra brown sugar.

23:03.002 --> 23:06.074
You sure you don't want
some fruit or something?

23:06.212 --> 23:08.179
No, thank you.
I'm fine. Thanks, ma'am.

23:08.317 --> 23:09.836
You let me know
if you need anything.

23:09.974 --> 23:11.631
Excuse me. Hi.Hi.

23:11.769 --> 23:14.151
I'm gonna need some hot sauce
for those hash browns

23:14.289 --> 23:18.604
and a little warm up, please.Sure thing.

23:25.093 --> 23:26.819
So how long
have you been in the Army?

23:26.957 --> 23:28.545
Just one second,
I'm sorry.

23:31.996 --> 23:33.342
All right, thank you.

23:33.481 --> 23:35.034
Uh, it's been 11 years.

23:35.172 --> 23:36.553
I plan on doing another nine

23:36.691 --> 23:38.624
and hopefully retiring
a Sergeant Major.

23:38.762 --> 23:40.419
Then I want to focus on my art.

23:40.557 --> 23:44.802
Who's your favorite artist?You ask a lot of questions.

23:46.563 --> 23:48.910
Occupational hazard.Mm.

23:49.048 --> 23:51.947
Well, if you must know,
I have two.

23:52.085 --> 23:53.086
Georges Seurat?

23:53.224 --> 23:54.985
Yeah.

23:55.123 --> 23:56.952
And Claude Monet.
You heard of him?

23:57.090 --> 23:58.920
Of course.

23:59.058 --> 24:00.646
He's my number one.

24:00.784 --> 24:03.925
I mean, I mess around a bit with
pointillism but Monet's style?

24:04.063 --> 24:05.996
I mean, who's messing with him?

24:07.342 --> 24:10.725
You, um,
got a little bit right...

24:10.863 --> 24:12.278
Oh.Some right here.

24:12.416 --> 24:14.073
Other side.

24:14.211 --> 24:17.179
Just-- All right,
you smudged it. Let me...

24:17.317 --> 24:20.838
You mind?Uh-- No.

24:20.976 --> 24:23.807
Got a little bit. Yep.

24:24.946 --> 24:25.809
Thanks.

24:25.947 --> 24:28.363
Mm-hm.

24:28.501 --> 24:32.160
You know, I saw some of Monet's
work at the Met in New York.

24:32.298 --> 24:34.024
I've never been to New York.

24:34.162 --> 24:36.820
It's so different when you can
see the brushstrokes up close.

24:36.958 --> 24:39.512
And I've actually never seen
a real Monet in person.

24:39.650 --> 24:40.824
Mm.

24:40.962 --> 24:42.481
You should get up there
sometime.

24:44.621 --> 24:46.036
To see the painting?

24:51.593 --> 24:52.836
Maybe I will.

24:57.806 --> 24:59.739
Ooh! Look at that.

24:59.877 --> 25:03.087
[CHUCKLES]
Yeah, baby.

25:03.225 --> 25:04.986
Hey.Hey, Charles!

25:05.124 --> 25:07.575
Hey, come on over
and meet First Sergeant King.

25:07.713 --> 25:09.611
Gentlemen.Just call them fellas.

25:09.749 --> 25:11.682
[ALL CHUCKLE]

25:11.820 --> 25:14.582
Why in the world would anybody
want to do that?

25:14.720 --> 25:16.791
I don't understand.
You know what I'm saying?

25:16.929 --> 25:19.069
Oh, what? It's not.
You're getting very upset.

25:19.207 --> 25:20.933
[IMITATING ENGINE DRONING]

25:21.071 --> 25:22.762
[ALL LAUGH]

25:22.900 --> 25:25.972
Well, I thought men were
luxuries, not necessities.

25:26.110 --> 25:29.113
You just wanna stand there
or you gonna come help me?

25:29.251 --> 25:31.253
You're lucky you saw him first.

25:34.118 --> 25:36.431
Appreciate you coming by, son.I appreciate the food.

25:36.569 --> 25:38.157
Anytime.Yeah.

25:38.295 --> 25:39.538
We'll see you again soon, hon.

25:39.676 --> 25:41.436
Okay?Yes. Of course.

25:41.574 --> 25:44.922
You leaving already?I am. Yes, ma'am.

25:46.337 --> 25:48.892
I mean, yes, I am.Are you sure?

25:49.030 --> 25:51.273
I was just about
to put out dessert.

25:51.411 --> 25:54.967
I wish that I could.Fresh apple pie.

25:55.105 --> 25:57.107
I got a phone date
with my daughter.

25:57.245 --> 25:58.695
Oh.

25:58.833 --> 26:00.697
Yeah, she lives in Texas
with her mother,

26:00.835 --> 26:03.941
and I gotta catch her
before she goes to sleep.

26:04.079 --> 26:05.287
Of course.

26:07.220 --> 26:08.808
Well, if you're ever
in New York

26:08.946 --> 26:11.570
and wanna see that Monet,
look me up.

26:13.295 --> 26:14.573
Will do.

26:15.884 --> 26:17.714
Now, take care.You too.

26:24.548 --> 26:25.584
[CHUCKLES]

26:27.378 --> 26:28.794
What?

26:28.932 --> 26:30.519
[CHAKA KHAN'S "I KNOW YOU,
I LIVE YOU" PLAYING]

26:42.946 --> 26:44.810
[RINGING]

26:44.948 --> 26:47.433
[TV DRONING INDISTINCTLY]

26:47.571 --> 26:49.262
Hello?

26:49.400 --> 26:51.195
Hi, can I speak to Dana,
please?

26:51.333 --> 26:53.784
This is she. Hey.

26:53.922 --> 26:56.304
This is First Sergeant
Charles King.

26:56.442 --> 26:58.409
Oh.

26:58.547 --> 27:00.515
Hello, Charles.

27:00.653 --> 27:03.691
My dad told me
he gave you my number.

27:03.829 --> 27:05.278
Three weeks ago.

27:05.416 --> 27:07.764
Yeah. Um...

27:07.902 --> 27:09.420
Is now a good time to talk?

27:09.558 --> 27:11.146
[INHALES DEEPLY]
Mm...

27:11.284 --> 27:13.459
I am kind of in the middle
of something.

27:13.597 --> 27:16.565
Oh, okay, I can call you back.

27:16.704 --> 27:19.120
No. No, that's fine.
I have a few minutes.

27:20.915 --> 27:23.849
Listen, Dana, I would have
called you sooner.

27:25.644 --> 27:26.817
But...

27:30.165 --> 27:32.478
I just... I wanna be honest

27:32.616 --> 27:37.517
and my divorce just got final.

27:39.312 --> 27:41.487
I don't want to make things
harder for you, Charles.

27:41.625 --> 27:45.249
No, but you're not. You're not.

27:45.387 --> 27:48.080
That's exactly why
I'm calling you right now.

27:48.218 --> 27:50.427
You've got your daughter
to think about.

27:50.565 --> 27:53.361
And I'm always gonna be
thinking about her.

27:53.499 --> 27:55.259
You know,
it's not gonna change.

27:55.397 --> 27:58.849
But I just want you to know

27:58.987 --> 28:01.369
that you don't have anything
to worry about.

28:02.611 --> 28:03.578
I promise.

28:06.339 --> 28:07.340
Fair enough.

28:15.452 --> 28:16.384
Hello?

28:18.766 --> 28:21.354
Dana, I want you to know
I've been thinking about you.

28:23.322 --> 28:24.357
A lot.

28:26.946 --> 28:30.294
Well, you have had three weeks.

28:54.111 --> 28:56.631
Okay, okay,
let's blow them out. Ready?

28:56.769 --> 28:58.806
[BOTH LAUGHING]

28:58.944 --> 29:00.221
Yay!

29:00.359 --> 29:04.190
Okay, now,
let's get all sugared up.

29:04.328 --> 29:05.951
Here we go.

29:06.089 --> 29:07.953
[WHOOPING]

29:08.091 --> 29:10.472
[NE-YO'S "MISS INDEPENDENT"
PLAYING ON RADIO]

29:13.924 --> 29:15.098
Okay.

29:17.272 --> 29:20.966
All right, time out.

29:21.104 --> 29:22.830
Mommy needs a little break.

29:27.351 --> 29:29.837
Peek-a-boo, Daddy!

29:29.975 --> 29:32.046
What are you talking about?

29:34.911 --> 29:37.430
What?Okay.

29:37.568 --> 29:38.777
What are you looking at?

29:38.915 --> 29:40.364
[RADIO STOPS PLAYING]

29:40.502 --> 29:42.297
What are you saying,
silly boy?

29:42.435 --> 29:43.678
Peek-a-boo, Daddy!

29:46.129 --> 29:48.994
[]

30:58.408 --> 31:01.756
[STEVIE WONDER'S
"FOR ONCE IN MY LIFE" PLAYING]

31:09.074 --> 31:11.352
[PHONE RINGING]

31:15.528 --> 31:16.840
Hello?

31:16.978 --> 31:18.497
Hey, it's Charles.
How you doing?

31:18.635 --> 31:21.603
[SIGHS]
Better now.

31:21.741 --> 31:24.572
There's barely any Black people,
let alone Black women.

31:24.710 --> 31:26.608
No second chances if I mess up.

31:26.746 --> 31:28.610
It's like
I'm the standard bearer

31:28.748 --> 31:31.234
for every other Black person
who wants to work there.

31:31.372 --> 31:33.132
I understand that.

31:33.270 --> 31:35.997
But you do love what you do,
right?

31:36.135 --> 31:39.173
It's the New York Times.
Of course I love it.

31:39.311 --> 31:41.485
For a journalist,
that's the dream come true.

31:41.623 --> 31:45.627
It's the only time I hate New
York, when it's hot and muggy.

31:45.765 --> 31:50.322
New York is not hot.
Iraq, now, that's hot.

31:50.460 --> 31:51.633
You've been to Iraq?

31:51.771 --> 31:54.257
Kuwait too. Desert Storm.

31:54.395 --> 31:57.363
Wow, was it bad?

31:57.501 --> 31:59.227
Bad enough.

32:01.298 --> 32:02.851
Listen, can I
call you back later?

32:02.990 --> 32:04.508
I got a meeting with the brass
in a few,

32:04.646 --> 32:07.063
and I do not want to be late.

32:07.201 --> 32:09.306
Yeah, of course.
Call me tomorrow.

32:09.444 --> 32:11.377
All right, bye.

32:11.515 --> 32:12.896
Bye.

32:15.899 --> 32:17.452
Hang up.

32:17.590 --> 32:19.765
You hang up.

32:19.903 --> 32:21.456
No, you hang up.

32:21.594 --> 32:23.182
Are we really doing this
right now?

32:23.320 --> 32:24.839
I guess we are.

32:24.977 --> 32:26.841
Okay.

32:26.979 --> 32:29.361
[CHUCKLES]
Are you gonna hang up the phone?

32:29.499 --> 32:31.466
Bye.

32:32.916 --> 32:33.952
Bye.

32:36.678 --> 32:39.819
So do you think you'll want
more kids?

32:39.958 --> 32:43.030
Definitely.
I always wanted a big family.

32:45.860 --> 32:47.344
How's your daughter handling it?

32:47.482 --> 32:50.382
Christina? She's great.

32:50.520 --> 32:53.799
Beautiful. She listens. Smart.

32:55.801 --> 32:58.010
Lot smarter than me,
I'll tell you that.

33:00.840 --> 33:01.980
Hold on one second.

33:07.675 --> 33:09.366
Um...

33:09.504 --> 33:10.989
You know, it was, uh...

33:13.853 --> 33:15.200
It was stressful.

33:17.719 --> 33:21.965
It was stressful for everybody.

33:22.103 --> 33:25.003
Well, how did you handle it?

33:25.141 --> 33:27.488
How did I handle it?
It was, um...

33:35.047 --> 33:36.324
I felt like a failure.

33:41.226 --> 33:42.503
Tried to make it work.

33:44.988 --> 33:48.647
But, you know, we were young.

33:48.785 --> 33:53.859
We were kids
trying to figure it out and...

33:55.723 --> 34:01.729
you know, we both were to blame,
you know, so...

34:07.459 --> 34:08.494
It hurt.

34:11.739 --> 34:13.361
Well, I'm sorry you were hurt.

34:13.499 --> 34:16.606
Hey, no, it's...

34:16.744 --> 34:20.748
You know, I'm doing good.

34:22.405 --> 34:24.545
And I love being a father.

34:24.683 --> 34:27.168
You know, one of the best things
that ever happened to me.

34:31.241 --> 34:33.001
And if I didn't go through that,

34:33.140 --> 34:36.108
I wouldn't be talking to you,
so...

34:36.246 --> 34:37.765
Sometimes after dinner,

34:37.903 --> 34:41.596
my father would announce
he was going to buy milk.

34:41.734 --> 34:46.429
I never understood how my mom
could just sit there

34:46.567 --> 34:48.155
with her head down.

34:49.432 --> 34:52.090
She knew he was
having an affair.

34:52.228 --> 34:53.953
Hell, the whole town did.

34:56.749 --> 35:02.169
One night, I came down
with this terrible flu,

35:02.307 --> 35:04.481
and my mom had to borrow
the neighbor's car

35:04.619 --> 35:06.311
to take me to the hospital.

35:08.347 --> 35:13.007
And I just remember lying there
on that back seat, delirious.

35:15.216 --> 35:17.356
When I lifted my head up,

35:17.494 --> 35:18.978
I saw we were driving around

35:19.117 --> 35:22.430
a parking lot of a bar
on the base.

35:22.568 --> 35:26.020
How old were you?I was 7.

35:27.987 --> 35:30.128
She was looking for his car.

35:33.131 --> 35:37.169
Did she ever find it?No.

35:42.209 --> 35:44.763
He used to say
that she trapped him

35:44.901 --> 35:46.868
by getting pregnant with me.

35:48.836 --> 35:51.459
She was just as trapped
as he was.

35:54.221 --> 35:55.808
Wow.

35:58.846 --> 36:00.710
How'd that make you feel?

36:06.923 --> 36:09.374
Now, see... Mm-mm.

36:09.512 --> 36:12.411
You are all up in my business.

36:12.549 --> 36:14.413
Trying to get me all open.

36:14.551 --> 36:17.520
Well, sounds a little too late
for that.

36:17.658 --> 36:19.349
What did you say?

36:19.487 --> 36:20.833
You heard me.

36:22.973 --> 36:24.803
No, I'm just playing.

36:24.941 --> 36:27.357
Enough about me.

36:29.394 --> 36:30.774
So, what do you do?

36:30.912 --> 36:33.950
When you're not turning
young men into soldiers.

36:34.088 --> 36:39.852
Well, if I'm not drawing
or painting...

36:43.028 --> 36:44.236
probably in the gym.

36:44.374 --> 36:47.757
Okay. I like the gym too.

36:47.895 --> 36:52.865
For the massages, and the little
smoothies at the juice bar.

36:55.489 --> 36:58.457
Are you telling me you go to
the gym and you don't work out?

36:58.595 --> 37:03.221
Well, I'm not exactly
the workout type.

37:04.636 --> 37:06.603
But I stay active.

37:06.741 --> 37:08.087
It's a walking city.

37:11.021 --> 37:14.301
Well, the massages

37:14.439 --> 37:19.616
or juices, smoothies, all that,

37:19.754 --> 37:21.411
whatever it is you're doing...

37:24.449 --> 37:25.967
it's working.

37:28.073 --> 37:30.144
I think you are beautiful.

37:34.424 --> 37:37.013
So you like this guy or not?I can't. He's a soldier.

37:37.151 --> 37:38.601
My dad was a soldier.

37:38.739 --> 37:40.706
It's not like he walks around
in uniform all the time.

37:40.844 --> 37:42.536
That shit would be hot though,
boo-boo.

37:42.674 --> 37:43.675
Oh, girl!

37:43.813 --> 37:45.608
And he's divorced.

37:45.746 --> 37:47.092
And he has
a 9-year-old daughter.

37:47.230 --> 37:48.783
So?Is he a good dad?

37:48.921 --> 37:50.164
He seems like it.

37:50.302 --> 37:51.545
I don't know. I don't know.

37:51.683 --> 37:53.340
He is not exactly my type.

37:53.478 --> 37:56.032
Look, you said he was nice,
right?

37:56.170 --> 37:57.205
Mm-hm.

37:57.344 --> 38:00.347
And he's cute too?God, yes.

38:00.485 --> 38:01.727
So, what's your problem?

38:01.865 --> 38:03.039
Are you too good for him?

38:03.177 --> 38:05.352
You little bougie bitch.

38:05.490 --> 38:06.974
I barely know him.

38:07.112 --> 38:08.665
We've only talked on the phone.

38:08.803 --> 38:11.116
If you decide to let him visit,
don't shave your legs.

38:11.254 --> 38:12.980
What?I know you.

38:13.118 --> 38:14.878
There is no way you would ever
sleep with a guy,

38:15.016 --> 38:16.432
at least not the first time,

38:16.570 --> 38:19.020
without exfoliating,
moisturizing, and shaving.

38:19.158 --> 38:20.919
God, it's true.

38:21.057 --> 38:22.300
Same.

38:23.749 --> 38:25.682
Sorry I can't come pick you up.

38:25.820 --> 38:28.236
Don't worry about it.
I know you got work.

38:28.375 --> 38:31.067
If you get lucky with traffic,
you should be here about30.

38:31.205 --> 38:33.172
You know, I could
just stay in a hotel.

38:33.311 --> 38:34.864
It's not a problem.

38:35.002 --> 38:37.487
Of course not.
Don't be silly.

38:37.625 --> 38:40.352
I mean, unless-- Well,
do you wanna stay at a hotel?

38:40.490 --> 38:44.218
No. No, I'm good.

38:44.356 --> 38:49.050
Good. Okay, good.

38:49.188 --> 38:51.398
Oh, and by the way,
that cab ride from LaGuardia

38:51.536 --> 38:53.572
shouldn't cost you
more than 30 bucks.

38:53.710 --> 38:56.679
I usually tip
if he helps me with my bags.

38:56.817 --> 38:58.922
And don't let him take
the Queensboro Bridge.

38:59.060 --> 39:00.545
Okay, general.

39:00.683 --> 39:02.098
Hopefully, all my training

39:02.236 --> 39:04.307
and the tank battles
I survived in Iraq

39:04.445 --> 39:06.792
have prepared me enough
for New York City.

39:06.930 --> 39:08.863
As you were, Negro.

39:09.001 --> 39:11.832
And if I don't make it... Oh, God.

39:11.970 --> 39:13.627
I want you to know
that I tried.

39:13.765 --> 39:16.077
Can you call my mama for me and
just tell her that I love her?

39:16.215 --> 39:17.976
Charles, you can stop now.

39:18.114 --> 39:19.667
Guess what.

39:19.805 --> 39:20.979
Huh?

39:21.117 --> 39:22.912
Guess.What?

39:23.050 --> 39:24.879
Chicken butt.

39:25.017 --> 39:27.226
You are so corny.

39:27.365 --> 39:29.505
Get off the phone!

39:29.643 --> 39:31.265
[PHONE RINGS]

39:31.403 --> 39:32.680
Hey, are you there?

39:32.818 --> 39:35.511
Yes, ma'am. I'm right here.

39:35.649 --> 39:36.753
I'm sorry, Manny.

39:36.891 --> 39:38.410
No problem, Ms. Canedy.

39:38.548 --> 39:41.068
Your guest has arrived.
Do you want me to send him up?

39:41.206 --> 39:42.725
Yes, please.
I left the key for him.

39:42.863 --> 39:44.105
Yes, ma'am,
I got it right here.

39:44.243 --> 39:45.279
Can you put him on real quick?

39:45.417 --> 39:48.351
Sure.
She wants to talk to you.

39:48.489 --> 39:50.940
Hey, just wanna let you know
that I made it in safe.

39:51.078 --> 39:52.010
Mission accomplished.

39:52.148 --> 39:53.977
[CHUCKLES]
Happy to hear.

39:54.115 --> 39:56.290
So I'm not gonna be home
for another couple hours.

39:56.428 --> 39:58.603
Yeah, that's fine.
I got my sketchbook with me,

39:58.741 --> 40:00.259
so handle your work.Okay.

40:00.398 --> 40:02.020
Help yourself to anything
in the fridge.

40:02.158 --> 40:04.747
I'll do that. See you later?[MOUTHS] It's him.

40:04.885 --> 40:07.094
Can you put Manny back on? Sure. Hold on.

40:07.232 --> 40:08.440
Yes, ma'am.

40:08.578 --> 40:10.822
Manny, it's his first time
in New York,

40:10.960 --> 40:13.825
help him if he needs anything. Yes, ma'am.

40:13.963 --> 40:16.793
Can you see if he has on
kind of worn-out sneakers?

40:16.931 --> 40:21.453
Probably dirty?Yes, ma'am.

40:21.591 --> 40:25.561
Okay. You can send him up. All right.

40:26.941 --> 40:28.149
She says you can go on up.

40:28.287 --> 40:29.254
All right, perfect.

40:29.392 --> 40:31.325
Thanks, man.You got it.

40:33.948 --> 40:34.880
He there?

40:35.018 --> 40:36.399
Mm-hm.

40:36.537 --> 40:38.401
What are you doing?
Get out of here!

40:38.539 --> 40:40.230
No! I have too much work to do.

40:40.368 --> 40:42.923
Work, shmerk! Go get some!

40:43.061 --> 40:45.926
[]

40:47.997 --> 40:48.929
Here you go.

40:53.002 --> 40:55.142
Ms. Canedy.Manny.

40:55.280 --> 40:57.178
[CHUCKLES]

41:17.682 --> 41:19.580
[LOCK CLICKS]

41:22.963 --> 41:23.929
Hey, you.

41:24.067 --> 41:25.621
How was your day?

41:25.759 --> 41:26.967
It was good.

41:27.105 --> 41:29.107
How was your flight?

41:29.245 --> 41:30.488
It was good.

41:31.592 --> 41:32.869
Welcome home.

41:33.007 --> 41:35.320
[CHUCKLES]

41:35.458 --> 41:37.391
Mm.

41:37.529 --> 41:39.704
You smell good.Thank you.

41:39.842 --> 41:41.395
I got something for you.

41:45.157 --> 41:47.919
This is for you.

41:48.057 --> 41:49.507
Oh, my God.

41:49.645 --> 41:51.819
You like it?

41:51.957 --> 41:53.234
I do.

41:53.372 --> 41:56.514
I really tried to imagine you
in my head.

42:02.209 --> 42:05.074
What?I'm lying.

42:05.212 --> 42:08.180
I used that photo over there.Oh, my God.

42:09.768 --> 42:10.942
Glad you like it.

42:12.530 --> 42:14.048
So I know you just got here,

42:14.186 --> 42:18.225
but we should probably talk
about sleeping arrangements.

42:18.363 --> 42:21.539
I have a sofa bed.
It's pretty comfortable.

42:23.713 --> 42:25.025
That's fine.

42:25.163 --> 42:27.752
I have no problem
sleeping on the couch.

42:27.890 --> 42:29.029
Why you look nervous?

42:29.167 --> 42:30.548
What did you think
I was gonna say?

42:30.686 --> 42:32.446
I don't look nervous.

42:32.584 --> 42:35.794
I just didn't want to set up
any unrealistic expectations.

42:35.932 --> 42:38.866
Mm-hm. Well, I expect
to have a good time.

42:40.247 --> 42:42.836
I'm not worried.
I'll be with you.

42:49.636 --> 42:54.917
Okay. Have we decided?We have. Uh...

42:55.055 --> 42:57.782
I'm ready. Are you?Yeah.

42:57.920 --> 43:00.129
What is that?Olive oil.

43:01.751 --> 43:03.650
I'll have the linguini
with clam sauce, please,

43:03.788 --> 43:05.755
and a caprese salad to start.Absolutely.

43:05.893 --> 43:08.827
And for you, sir?I'll have the Caesar salad.

43:08.965 --> 43:09.828
That's it?

43:11.278 --> 43:13.004
I'm sorry, can you give us
one minute?

43:13.142 --> 43:15.075
Of course.Thank you.

43:15.213 --> 43:16.352
What?

43:16.490 --> 43:18.354
You can get
a Caesar salad anywhere.

43:18.492 --> 43:20.770
Try the pasta.That's a lot of carbs.

43:20.908 --> 43:23.635
You eat mess hall food all day.
Come on.

43:23.773 --> 43:27.501
How do you know
what I like to eat? Hmm?

43:29.814 --> 43:33.334
Well, at least get some grilled
chicken in it or something.

43:36.717 --> 43:37.787
Okay.

43:46.900 --> 43:48.487
I really am glad you're here.

43:48.626 --> 43:51.801
I just want you to enjoy
your weekend and a have good--

43:59.188 --> 44:01.190
You taste like oregano.

44:11.545 --> 44:13.512
What kind of theater
is that?

44:13.651 --> 44:15.653
That's an off-Broadway theater.

44:15.791 --> 44:18.069
So we're near Broadway.No.

44:18.207 --> 44:22.038
See, there's off-Broadway,
and there's off-off-Broadway.

44:22.176 --> 44:25.076
Okay, so is there anything
actually on Broadway?

44:25.214 --> 44:28.907
[CHUCKLES]
Yes, but it's not
about the street.

44:29.045 --> 44:32.083
It's all about the size
of the house.

44:32.221 --> 44:34.948
The house?How many seats there are.

44:36.466 --> 44:38.745
In the house?Yes.

44:38.883 --> 44:41.644
Okay. In a theater house.Yes.

44:41.782 --> 44:42.956
Just like I thought.

44:49.583 --> 44:51.758
Charles, please.
I appreciate the manners,

44:51.896 --> 44:54.243
but you can't keep walking
on the outside of the sidewalk.

44:54.381 --> 44:56.728
It's New York.
There are too many people.

44:56.866 --> 44:58.350
I'm sorry.
I just can't help it.

44:59.938 --> 45:04.218
Just--
It's a force of habit.

45:05.806 --> 45:08.775
You know what?
No, I'm sorry. Thank you.

45:08.913 --> 45:10.638
The world needs more gentlemen.

45:15.436 --> 45:18.301
That's an off-off-Broadway
kiss.

45:23.237 --> 45:25.170
That's an off-Broadway kiss.

45:26.758 --> 45:28.380
And this is...

45:35.905 --> 45:37.355
Broadway.

45:39.702 --> 45:43.154
And the Tony Award
for best kiss goes to...

45:43.292 --> 45:46.260
No, hold on a second.
Who the hell is Tony?

45:48.055 --> 45:48.918
Easy.

45:56.305 --> 45:58.479
Uh, I'm gonna go freshen up
really quick.

45:58.617 --> 46:02.035
There's water and stuff
in the fridge,

46:02.173 --> 46:05.935
so help yourself to whatever.Okay.

46:12.355 --> 46:13.909
[DOOR CLOSES]

46:21.433 --> 46:23.470
[SOFTLY]
She's so fine.

46:38.796 --> 46:39.900
No.

47:07.376 --> 47:08.687
Do you need anything?

47:11.898 --> 47:16.834
Uh, yeah, maybe just a couple
extra pillows and a blanket.

47:16.972 --> 47:18.732
That red wine got me sleepy.

47:20.699 --> 47:24.358
I was thinking maybe you could
sleep on one side of the bed.

47:26.050 --> 47:26.913
If you want.

47:30.054 --> 47:33.057
Yeah. Yeah, that'd be cool.

47:34.334 --> 47:36.198
[WATER RUNNING]

47:50.039 --> 47:51.523
[CLEARS THROAT]

48:39.399 --> 48:40.607
We should stop.

48:40.745 --> 48:41.953
Huh?

48:44.300 --> 48:48.304
Yeah, sorry. Uh...
It's all that oregano.

49:01.524 --> 49:03.009
Good night.

49:05.149 --> 49:06.460
Good night.

49:14.641 --> 49:17.506
[CHARLES GRUNTING, PANTING]

49:50.125 --> 49:52.782
Who travels
with exercise equipment?

49:52.920 --> 49:54.646
I do.

49:54.784 --> 49:57.718
You slept good.I slept well.

49:58.926 --> 49:59.962
You slept well.

50:08.177 --> 50:11.663
Now, you need
to put all that away.

50:11.801 --> 50:13.700
I have not had my coffee yet.

50:15.357 --> 50:17.945
I remembered.
You like it black, right?

50:20.155 --> 50:22.053
Yes, I do.

50:22.191 --> 50:26.885
All right, so I'm gonna
need you to get up,

50:27.024 --> 50:30.544
get in the shower, get dressed,
then we'll go for a run.

50:30.682 --> 50:33.858
But I wanna see more
of your city. Okay?

50:36.826 --> 50:37.896
[LAUGHS]

50:38.035 --> 50:40.382
And I wanna see
more of your city.

50:40.520 --> 50:42.694
I'll take your state,
your zip code.

50:42.832 --> 50:44.282
I wanna see your area code.

50:44.420 --> 50:46.388
I wanna see your social
security number.

50:46.526 --> 50:48.252
I wanna see your passport,

50:48.390 --> 50:51.772
your military ID,
your blood type.

50:51.910 --> 50:53.602
Show it all to me.

50:53.740 --> 50:56.260
Oh, my God! I wanna see it all!

50:58.089 --> 51:01.023
[]

51:02.749 --> 51:04.509
Mmm!Mm-hm.

51:06.166 --> 51:08.651
Mm-hm.I told you.

51:08.789 --> 51:11.930
You really trying to corrupt me.You know you like it.

51:18.454 --> 51:21.285
So when are you
gonna show me this Monet?

51:21.423 --> 51:23.080
Saving the best for last.

51:26.255 --> 51:29.500
You know, I can't show you
the whole city in one weekend.

51:35.299 --> 51:37.232
Then I guess I gotta come back.

52:10.161 --> 52:11.162
Wait.What? What?

52:11.300 --> 52:12.577
I have to take a shower.Now?

52:12.715 --> 52:14.234
Yes, now. Because.No, no, why?

52:14.372 --> 52:15.718
No.No.

52:15.856 --> 52:17.168
I'll be right back.

52:28.214 --> 52:30.147
[DOOR OPENS]

52:39.846 --> 52:42.020
I'll keep that in mind.

52:42.159 --> 52:43.815
Close the drapes.

52:46.680 --> 52:47.992
I got you.

53:06.735 --> 53:09.634
[]

53:34.935 --> 53:36.282
Slow down.

54:01.203 --> 54:02.515
You like it?

54:07.036 --> 54:08.624
I love it.

54:11.178 --> 54:12.387
It's so beautiful.

54:19.325 --> 54:20.740
Thank you.

54:35.686 --> 54:38.205
[IMITATING BUGLE PLAYING
"REVEILLE"]

54:39.448 --> 54:40.449
What?

54:43.314 --> 54:44.902
What are you doing
up before me?

54:45.040 --> 54:47.249
We've only got four days,
soldier.

54:47.387 --> 54:48.837
It's Christmas time in New York.

54:48.975 --> 54:50.252
Up and at them.

54:53.151 --> 54:55.913
[DONNY HATHAWAY
"THIS CHRISTMAS" PLAYING]

55:04.646 --> 55:06.717
Are you done yet?

55:06.855 --> 55:08.512
Yeah.

55:08.650 --> 55:11.756
Well, come on out.
Let me see.

55:14.587 --> 55:17.244
Charles, get out here, please.

55:22.042 --> 55:23.250
Oh, yes.

55:23.389 --> 55:24.907
I-I don't know.

55:25.045 --> 55:29.878
Let's try the blazer. Come on.

55:30.016 --> 55:31.845
I look like
somebody's accountant.

55:31.983 --> 55:33.778
Mm-hm. A fine one.

55:33.916 --> 55:36.436
And do you know how expensive
these clothes are?

55:36.574 --> 55:38.576
It's a Christmas gift.

55:38.714 --> 55:41.372
No, I can't let you do that.I want to.

55:41.510 --> 55:43.512
I know you don't care
about clothes.

55:43.650 --> 55:45.963
Because clothes
don't make the man, baby.

55:46.101 --> 55:48.483
But the man can make
the clothes, baby.

55:48.621 --> 55:50.830
Besides, you work hard.

55:50.968 --> 55:54.385
You deserve more than just
baggy jeans and T-shirts.

55:54.523 --> 55:56.249
I like my jeans.Okay.

55:56.387 --> 55:58.078
Well, what about
the grandpa sneakers?

55:58.216 --> 55:59.942
Grandpa?

56:00.080 --> 56:02.497
The only place you should be
wearing those to is the gym.

56:02.635 --> 56:04.015
They're practical
and comfortable.

56:04.153 --> 56:07.502
And those aren't?
Come on, now.

56:07.640 --> 56:10.815
Don't act like
you don't like it.

56:13.404 --> 56:17.926
Look at you. Smile. See?

56:21.170 --> 56:23.103
Fine.

56:23.241 --> 56:25.071
I'm keeping my sneakers,
I'm paying for half.

56:25.209 --> 56:26.383
Charles!Half!

56:29.386 --> 56:30.835
Baby.Hmm?

56:30.973 --> 56:32.319
I want you
to be my girlfriend.

56:32.458 --> 56:34.114
What?

56:34.252 --> 56:37.739
I want you to be my lady.
Like, officially.

56:37.877 --> 56:42.640
What do you mean,
like, go steady?

56:42.778 --> 56:45.332
You know exactly
what that means.
Heh.

56:45.471 --> 56:49.267
That's funny?No. It's just--

56:49.406 --> 56:52.443
It's just what?We're grown.

56:52.581 --> 56:55.895
Yeah. We're grown enough
to commit to one another.

56:57.448 --> 56:58.898
Charles.

56:59.036 --> 57:00.589
Don't say my name like that.

57:00.727 --> 57:02.142
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

57:02.280 --> 57:04.282
Can we talk about this later?I want to now.

57:04.421 --> 57:05.870
We have guests.They can wait.

57:08.873 --> 57:09.943
Please?

57:14.292 --> 57:16.260
- Merry Christmas!- Hi.

57:16.398 --> 57:17.951
Merry Christmas!

57:21.161 --> 57:23.854
However,
I don't want her hurt.

57:23.992 --> 57:25.234
I don't want her hurt.No, no.

57:25.372 --> 57:26.788
That's not
my intention at all.

57:26.926 --> 57:29.273
I know it's not your intentions,
but it may happen.

57:29.411 --> 57:31.378
He actually said
officially?

57:31.517 --> 57:34.002
That's the sweetest thing
I ever heard.
Oh, my God.

57:34.140 --> 57:36.142
To die for.It is so corny.

57:36.280 --> 57:37.523
But he can't help it.
He's military.

57:37.661 --> 57:40.560
You can't help it.
You're falling for him.

57:40.698 --> 57:42.493
Yeah, you're sprung, boo-boo.I am not.

57:42.631 --> 57:44.184
I've never seen you
like this before.

57:44.322 --> 57:45.807
Like what?Like you like him.

57:45.945 --> 57:48.810
Of course I like him.No, I mean, you "like" like him.

57:48.948 --> 57:51.157
Like you really like him.

57:51.295 --> 57:52.952
I want a drink.You want wine or--

57:53.090 --> 57:55.851
It's Christmas, I need a drink.
I need a drink.

57:55.989 --> 57:59.959
But you're gonna be good to her.Yes, yes, ma'am, I am.

58:00.097 --> 58:02.237
You said--No, no, I want Scotch.

58:02.375 --> 58:03.894
You weren't kidding
about his ass.

58:04.032 --> 58:05.620
You could bounce a quarter
off that thing.

58:05.758 --> 58:07.484
'Tis the season.Ho, ho, ho.

58:07.622 --> 58:09.520
Just tell me one thing.Hmm?

58:09.658 --> 58:10.763
Is he good in bed?

58:12.454 --> 58:14.214
Now, you know we wouldn't be
talking if he weren't.

58:14.352 --> 58:15.388
[ALL EXCLAIM]

58:15.526 --> 58:16.562
Good God.

58:16.700 --> 58:18.909
I don't want that.Yeah.

58:19.047 --> 58:20.876
She's a good girl.She is a very good girl.

58:21.014 --> 58:23.154
She was a--
Don't talk to me like that.

58:23.292 --> 58:24.673
No, no, like a nice girl.

58:26.330 --> 58:28.781
Julie?Yeah, Ms. Judy.

58:28.919 --> 58:31.922
Yeah, she could talk.
She could talk.

58:32.060 --> 58:35.442
So you gonna answer my question?What question?

58:35.581 --> 58:36.858
The one we were
talking about earlier.

58:36.996 --> 58:39.792
Charles, you know
I care about you.

58:39.930 --> 58:42.553
Why do we have to define
our relationship?

58:42.691 --> 58:45.729
Because we have one.But what's the hurry?

58:45.867 --> 58:48.559
There's no hurry. We've just
been together for six months.

58:50.285 --> 58:52.218
I don't wanna give up my career
to follow you around

58:52.356 --> 58:53.875
to different military bases.

58:54.013 --> 58:55.601
Well, who said anything
about that?

58:55.739 --> 58:57.879
And you don't even live here.

58:58.017 --> 59:00.364
You seeing somebody else?What?

59:01.676 --> 59:04.748
Are you seeing somebody else?No.

59:06.819 --> 59:08.061
I'm serious.

59:10.547 --> 59:13.032
No. I'm not.

59:13.170 --> 59:16.276
I would never ask you to give up
your career just to follow me.

59:16.414 --> 59:17.761
You know that, right?

59:21.178 --> 59:22.282
Yeah, I know.

59:33.224 --> 59:37.643
I'm not saying this is gonna be
easy, but we can make this work.

59:42.095 --> 59:43.752
How can you be so sure?

59:47.411 --> 59:48.446
I can't.

59:50.138 --> 59:51.657
I can't predict
the future either,

59:51.795 --> 59:54.245
but I know
we got a shot at one.

59:59.596 --> 1:00:01.494
Do you trust me?

1:00:04.739 --> 1:00:06.050
Yeah.

1:00:09.916 --> 1:00:13.782
Then be my girlfriend.
Officially.

1:00:18.545 --> 1:00:20.064
I already am.

1:00:30.799 --> 1:00:33.664
[]

1:00:35.562 --> 1:00:38.980
You know you could've told me
that earlier, right?

1:00:39.118 --> 1:00:41.189
I had to make you work for it.

1:00:44.226 --> 1:00:45.987
Now it's about to be your turn.

1:00:48.679 --> 1:00:50.060
Lead the way.

1:00:58.793 --> 1:01:00.104
Leave them open.

1:01:05.696 --> 1:01:07.215
Baby.

1:01:19.848 --> 1:01:23.334
Slow down, slow down,
slow down.

1:01:23.472 --> 1:01:24.473
Hold up.

1:02:02.580 --> 1:02:04.237
Do you want a ride?

1:02:04.375 --> 1:02:06.688
Now, you know you don't wanna
drive to the airport

1:02:06.826 --> 1:02:08.103
this early in the morning.

1:02:08.241 --> 1:02:09.449
It's freezing out.

1:02:14.696 --> 1:02:16.767
And you could put this one
under the tree.

1:02:16.905 --> 1:02:19.252
Another one?This is for Manny.

1:02:19.390 --> 1:02:20.495
The doorman?

1:02:20.633 --> 1:02:22.497
It's a Mets hat.
He's from Queens.

1:02:22.635 --> 1:02:25.465
I didn't know you two
were friends.

1:02:25.603 --> 1:02:27.191
We're buddies.

1:02:27.329 --> 1:02:29.746
Oh, buddies.

1:02:31.851 --> 1:02:33.439
Bet you didn't know
he was a marine.

1:02:33.577 --> 1:02:36.787
No. He never mentioned it.

1:02:36.925 --> 1:02:38.685
That's because you two
aren't buddies.

1:02:40.653 --> 1:02:42.310
This is for you.

1:02:43.829 --> 1:02:45.278
It's a bunch of grandpa music?

1:02:45.416 --> 1:02:48.109
Hey, that's grown man music
right there.

1:02:48.247 --> 1:02:49.455
Crazy woman.

1:02:50.905 --> 1:02:52.630
Am I?

1:02:52.769 --> 1:02:55.323
What?Crazy.

1:02:57.739 --> 1:02:59.292
Absolutely not.

1:03:02.675 --> 1:03:06.748
I'm gonna call you when I land.Be careful.

1:03:06.886 --> 1:03:08.232
I will.

1:03:12.512 --> 1:03:14.963
You know, you can leave
some of your new stuff here.

1:03:16.620 --> 1:03:19.830
I can clear out
some closet space.

1:03:19.968 --> 1:03:21.418
If you want.

1:03:29.633 --> 1:03:32.532
[]

1:03:37.675 --> 1:03:39.574
[DOOR CLOSES]

1:04:07.326 --> 1:04:09.362
[PHONE RINGING]

1:04:19.890 --> 1:04:21.927
- Hello?- Guess what.

1:04:22.065 --> 1:04:23.756
Chicken butt.

1:04:23.894 --> 1:04:25.378
I'm serious.

1:04:25.516 --> 1:04:27.967
CHARLES [CHUCKLES]:
Okay, what?

1:04:28.105 --> 1:04:30.763
We're doing a whole series
on race in America.

1:04:30.901 --> 1:04:32.385
I'm writing one of the stories,

1:04:32.523 --> 1:04:34.525
and they want me
to be an editor too.

1:04:34.663 --> 1:04:37.183
This is the biggest opportunity
they've ever given me.

1:04:37.321 --> 1:04:38.875
Hey! Congratulations.

1:04:39.013 --> 1:04:40.600
But if I don't nail this,

1:04:40.738 --> 1:04:42.430
my career at theTimes
will literally be over.

1:04:42.568 --> 1:04:44.432
Woman, please. No, no, I'm not kidding.

1:04:44.570 --> 1:04:46.089
They'll fire me.

1:04:46.227 --> 1:04:47.953
I can't lose this job,
Charles.

1:04:48.091 --> 1:04:49.782
New York is too expensive,
and...

1:04:49.920 --> 1:04:53.165
Stop. Listen, they picked you
because you're qualified

1:04:53.303 --> 1:04:55.270
and you do outstanding work.

1:04:55.408 --> 1:04:56.823
I'm proud of you.

1:04:56.962 --> 1:04:58.411
Thank you, baby.

1:04:58.549 --> 1:05:02.105
And I can't wait to read
what you write.

1:05:02.243 --> 1:05:04.279
I gotta start flying to Akron
once a week

1:05:04.417 --> 1:05:06.523
before I write anything.

1:05:06.661 --> 1:05:08.490
Not looking forward to that.

1:05:08.628 --> 1:05:11.459
Okay, well, just give me
a couple weeks.

1:05:11.597 --> 1:05:13.047
Let me get my new soldiers
squared away,

1:05:13.185 --> 1:05:14.703
and I'll see
if I can fly down.

1:05:14.841 --> 1:05:17.327
Really? Yeah.

1:05:17.465 --> 1:05:18.880
I'd love that.

1:05:20.951 --> 1:05:22.815
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

1:05:22.953 --> 1:05:24.886
[LINE TRILLING]

1:05:26.612 --> 1:05:28.614
You've reached
First Sergeant Charles King.

1:05:28.752 --> 1:05:30.478
Please leave a message
after the beep.

1:05:30.616 --> 1:05:32.307
[BEEPS]Hey, sweetie.

1:05:32.445 --> 1:05:33.860
I made it back to Akron.

1:05:33.999 --> 1:05:36.622
I think all this traveling
has got me sick.

1:05:36.760 --> 1:05:38.037
Thank you.Thank you.

1:05:38.175 --> 1:05:42.490
Anyways, I, uh--
I can't wait to see you.

1:05:42.628 --> 1:05:44.837
Call me later. Bye.

1:05:44.975 --> 1:05:47.667
[LINE TRILLING]

1:05:47.805 --> 1:05:49.807
You've reached
First Sergeant Charles King.

1:05:49.946 --> 1:05:51.637
Please leave a message
after the beep.

1:05:51.775 --> 1:05:54.364
Charles, where are you?

1:05:54.502 --> 1:05:55.986
Starting to get worried.

1:05:58.816 --> 1:06:00.715
[PHONE RINGING]

1:06:03.166 --> 1:06:05.306
Charles?Hey, baby.

1:06:05.444 --> 1:06:08.240
Where are you? I'm at the hospital.

1:06:08.378 --> 1:06:10.518
One of my soldiers' wives
just had a baby.

1:06:10.656 --> 1:06:12.313
Well, I've been calling you.

1:06:12.451 --> 1:06:15.419
I'm sorry. I had to come
to the hospital to help him.

1:06:15.557 --> 1:06:17.490
Help him what?

1:06:17.628 --> 1:06:19.216
Dana, he's 19 years old.

1:06:19.354 --> 1:06:21.460
You know, he was scared.
He needed me.

1:06:21.598 --> 1:06:23.772
Well, they don't have phones
at the hospital?

1:06:23.910 --> 1:06:25.878
It was pretty hectic in here.

1:06:26.016 --> 1:06:27.949
I tried,
but I couldn't get away.

1:06:28.087 --> 1:06:29.778
Well, since when
is delivering babies

1:06:29.916 --> 1:06:31.470
a part of your
job description?

1:06:34.024 --> 1:06:35.888
How about we both
get some sleep tonight,

1:06:36.026 --> 1:06:37.821
and we'll talk about it
in the morning?

1:06:37.959 --> 1:06:40.341
It is morning.
And I'm sick as a dog

1:06:40.479 --> 1:06:42.481
and stuck in Akron, Ohio,
waiting for you.

1:06:42.619 --> 1:06:44.207
I thought you were
in a plane crash.

1:06:44.345 --> 1:06:46.174
I-I'm sorry.
I should've called you,

1:06:46.312 --> 1:06:48.107
but you know
I have to be there for my men.

1:06:48.245 --> 1:06:50.040
And what about me?

1:06:50.178 --> 1:06:51.559
Your official girlfriend.

1:06:51.697 --> 1:06:53.457
I haven't seen you
in two months.

1:06:53.595 --> 1:06:55.597
Baby, it's only been six weeks.

1:06:55.735 --> 1:06:59.084
Okay, I don't think you
understand how hurt I am.

1:06:59.222 --> 1:07:01.707
Dana,
his wife had complications.

1:07:01.845 --> 1:07:03.398
Well, what kind?

1:07:03.536 --> 1:07:06.056
I don't know exactly.

1:07:06.194 --> 1:07:10.026
So, you've been there all night
and you don't know anything?

1:07:10.164 --> 1:07:12.580
All I know is that
she needed a C-section.

1:07:12.718 --> 1:07:15.134
Hmm. I see.

1:07:16.998 --> 1:07:19.345
So maybe you're the one
that's seeing someone else.

1:07:19.483 --> 1:07:21.175
What?
That why
you missed your flight?

1:07:21.313 --> 1:07:24.799
What? No. No. No.

1:07:24.937 --> 1:07:27.388
You wanna talk to him? He's in
the other room with his wife.

1:07:27.526 --> 1:07:29.079
Charles,
you can get your soldiers

1:07:29.217 --> 1:07:30.425
to say anything that you want.

1:07:30.563 --> 1:07:32.082
Come on, Dana,
you're talking crazy.

1:07:32.220 --> 1:07:35.189
Crazy? I have been sitting
in a hotel room for hours

1:07:35.327 --> 1:07:36.707
waiting on you.Why would I lie?

1:07:36.845 --> 1:07:38.226
You did not even bother
to call me

1:07:38.364 --> 1:07:39.917
to let me know
that you're not coming.

1:07:40.056 --> 1:07:41.574
Relax.I don't need to relax.

1:07:41.712 --> 1:07:45.544
We're-- You-- I can't do this.
Goodbye.

1:07:52.482 --> 1:07:53.966
[CLEARS THROAT]

1:07:54.104 --> 1:07:58.004
[]

1:08:05.115 --> 1:08:07.600
Hey, Manny.Welcome back, Ms. Canedy.

1:08:07.738 --> 1:08:09.119
You got a delivery earlier.

1:08:09.257 --> 1:08:11.604
I hope you don't mind,
I put it upstairs.Thanks.

1:08:19.060 --> 1:08:20.786
What are you doing here?

1:08:22.098 --> 1:08:25.031
Dana, I screwed up.
And I'm sorry.

1:08:25.170 --> 1:08:26.999
No, no, you can't just show up
like this.

1:08:27.137 --> 1:08:28.794
We haven't spoken in weeks.

1:08:28.932 --> 1:08:30.589
Because you won't return
my calls.

1:08:30.727 --> 1:08:32.522
Because I didn't wanna
talk to you.

1:08:32.660 --> 1:08:35.525
I'm sorry I didn't show up
in Akron.

1:08:35.663 --> 1:08:37.630
You're right. I should've
called you that night.

1:08:37.768 --> 1:08:40.081
I had no idea where you were.

1:08:40.219 --> 1:08:41.807
Or who you were with.

1:08:41.945 --> 1:08:44.016
I wasn't with anybody.

1:08:46.467 --> 1:08:47.640
Dana.

1:08:49.539 --> 1:08:50.850
Baby.

1:08:52.852 --> 1:08:55.890
I'm-- I'm not your father.

1:08:57.788 --> 1:08:59.790
I will never be
with another woman.

1:09:01.689 --> 1:09:02.655
I love you.

1:09:02.793 --> 1:09:04.588
You don't love me.I do.

1:09:04.726 --> 1:09:06.314
No, you love your men.

1:09:07.557 --> 1:09:10.456
I'm just better looking.No. Dana.

1:09:11.526 --> 1:09:12.803
I love you.

1:09:16.255 --> 1:09:18.809
I might've given you
a reason to leave me, but...

1:09:20.639 --> 1:09:22.710
I'm never gonna leave you.

1:09:26.990 --> 1:09:28.336
I love you.

1:09:31.926 --> 1:09:33.169
I love you too.

1:09:35.619 --> 1:09:37.173
I'm not going anywhere.

1:09:40.314 --> 1:09:45.042
You can trust that. Okay?
You can trust that.

1:09:46.768 --> 1:09:48.667
Okay? Okay?

1:09:48.805 --> 1:09:51.670
[]

1:09:53.223 --> 1:09:58.090
I love you so much.
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

1:09:58.228 --> 1:09:59.885
I'm so sorry.

1:10:03.785 --> 1:10:05.718
You know, it's not
a bad color on you.

1:10:08.204 --> 1:10:10.344
Sometimes I forget
you're a soldier.

1:10:15.728 --> 1:10:18.041
Can I ask you a question?

1:10:18.179 --> 1:10:20.146
Have I ever been able
to stop you?

1:10:22.079 --> 1:10:23.564
What's combat like?

1:10:25.186 --> 1:10:27.913
My dad never talks
about Vietnam.

1:10:28.051 --> 1:10:29.846
You never talk about Iraq.

1:10:33.574 --> 1:10:35.679
To be honest,
I don't remember much.

1:10:37.716 --> 1:10:39.027
Smells.

1:10:40.822 --> 1:10:42.134
Sounds.

1:10:44.757 --> 1:10:49.245
Training kicks in,
so it's kind of a blur.

1:10:51.281 --> 1:10:53.318
Were you scared?

1:10:53.456 --> 1:10:55.112
Of course I was.

1:11:02.016 --> 1:11:06.400
Have you ever actually
killed someone?

1:11:22.899 --> 1:11:24.797
[SIGHS]

1:11:28.836 --> 1:11:31.839
How can you be a soldier
and believe in God?

1:11:31.977 --> 1:11:33.841
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING SOFTLY]

1:11:35.670 --> 1:11:37.396
I believe in evil too.

1:11:38.949 --> 1:11:41.607
Protecting people
who can't protect themselves.

1:11:51.617 --> 1:11:55.069
[CHANTING]
Hard work work!
Hard work work!

1:11:55.207 --> 1:11:57.036
And everyone's doing
another formation.

1:11:57.174 --> 1:12:00.005
Hey! What's wrong with you,
boy?

1:12:00.143 --> 1:12:04.389
Get your ass out of the line.
What's wrong with you, boy!

1:12:04.527 --> 1:12:06.425
Get your ass over here.
What's wrong with you?

1:12:06.563 --> 1:12:09.221
Your ass is out of formation.
March now! March!

1:12:09.359 --> 1:12:11.913
You know what I'm talking about?
They're sitting here, waiting.

1:12:12.051 --> 1:12:13.674
Yes, first sarge.Wagon wheel!

1:12:13.812 --> 1:12:15.745
Are you out of your mind?No, first sarge.

1:12:15.883 --> 1:12:16.953
We're out in the streets,
taking fire,

1:12:17.091 --> 1:12:18.403
you looking real weak here.

1:12:18.541 --> 1:12:19.956
You see these guys?Yes.

1:12:20.094 --> 1:12:21.854
They're willing to take
a bullet and die for you.

1:12:21.992 --> 1:12:24.547
Look at them.
They're willing to die for you.

1:12:24.685 --> 1:12:27.170
You tired? You tired?Yes, first sarge.

1:12:27.308 --> 1:12:29.206
Keep moving your feet.

1:12:29.345 --> 1:12:31.864
I'm gonna put you on my back.
It's no man left behind.

1:12:32.002 --> 1:12:34.591
No man left behind, you hear me?Yes, first sarge.

1:12:34.729 --> 1:12:36.213
Do I need to carry you?No.

1:12:36.352 --> 1:12:38.664
Get on my back
and I'll carry you!No!

1:12:38.802 --> 1:12:40.597
I know you're still smoking
those cigarettes.

1:12:40.735 --> 1:12:42.841
Yes, first sarge.You gotta get off that stuff.

1:12:42.979 --> 1:12:46.016
Come on. Get in my formation,
let's go.

1:12:46.154 --> 1:12:47.708
Let's go! Work, work.

1:12:47.846 --> 1:12:50.435
Come on, Imhoff! No more
slow asses, you feel me?

1:12:50.573 --> 1:12:53.645
There it is. Let him hear it!Hard work work.

1:12:54.853 --> 1:12:57.407
Hard work work.Work work.

1:12:57.545 --> 1:12:59.271
Hard work work.

1:13:02.101 --> 1:13:03.551
Excuse me.

1:13:03.689 --> 1:13:07.279
[PHONES RINGING][CLAMORING]

1:13:07.417 --> 1:13:09.385
Excuse me, sorry.

1:13:11.007 --> 1:13:12.974
[RINGING]

1:13:13.112 --> 1:13:14.562
Charles? Dana.

1:13:14.700 --> 1:13:16.288
You okay?Hey. Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

1:13:16.426 --> 1:13:17.634
You're safe?Yes, I'm safe.

1:13:17.772 --> 1:13:19.602
Where are you? I'm at the office.

1:13:19.740 --> 1:13:20.603
You watching this?

1:13:22.294 --> 1:13:24.883
Oh, my God. Oh, my God![PEOPLE SCREAMING]

1:13:25.021 --> 1:13:29.163
Another plane has just hit
into another building.

1:13:29.301 --> 1:13:31.061
I want you to go home
and don't leave.

1:13:31.199 --> 1:13:33.305
Call your parents, tell them
not to leave the house.

1:13:33.443 --> 1:13:35.411
Don't do anything till you
hear from me, got it?

1:13:35.549 --> 1:13:37.827
Yeah. Yes, I got it. I got it! Nothing.

1:13:37.965 --> 1:13:40.312
All right, I gotta go.Charles. Wait.

1:13:40.450 --> 1:13:42.452
Yes?Please be careful.

1:13:44.040 --> 1:13:45.421
You too.

1:13:45.559 --> 1:13:47.526
Okay. All right, bye.

1:13:51.047 --> 1:13:53.877
[THE MAIN INGREDIENT'S "YOU'VE
BEEN MY INSPIRATION" PLAYING]

1:14:18.868 --> 1:14:21.284
Hey, sweetie. How was school?Fine.

1:14:21.422 --> 1:14:22.837
[DOOR SLAMS]

1:14:35.332 --> 1:14:37.265
May I come in?No.

1:14:43.513 --> 1:14:45.204
Do you wanna talk?No.

1:14:47.379 --> 1:14:48.932
Jordan Monroe King, look at me.

1:14:52.177 --> 1:14:54.490
Oh, my God, baby, what happened?I got in a fight.

1:14:54.628 --> 1:14:56.561
With who?Lance.

1:14:56.699 --> 1:14:58.079
Oh, I'm calling the principal.

1:14:58.217 --> 1:14:59.564
And I wanna talk
to that boy's parents.

1:14:59.702 --> 1:15:00.875
Mom, no.

1:15:01.013 --> 1:15:03.740
Snitches get stitches.What?

1:15:03.878 --> 1:15:05.535
If I snitch, I'm dead.

1:15:07.330 --> 1:15:08.711
Jordan, why were you fighting?

1:15:10.091 --> 1:15:13.612
They called me a wigger.
A white nigger.

1:15:13.750 --> 1:15:18.237
They say all kinds of stuff.Like what?

1:15:18.375 --> 1:15:21.102
Like if I'm Black, how come
I'm not good at basketball?

1:15:21.240 --> 1:15:23.519
Oh, sweetie.

1:15:26.280 --> 1:15:29.317
They said my dad
wasn't a soldier.

1:15:29.455 --> 1:15:32.355
They said if he's Black,
he's probably in prison.

1:15:38.050 --> 1:15:39.396
Okay.

1:15:43.193 --> 1:15:44.712
Come with me.

1:15:47.543 --> 1:15:49.165
Take your coat off. Sit down.

1:15:51.719 --> 1:15:53.652
Am I in trouble?No.

1:16:00.728 --> 1:16:01.902
Read it.

1:16:05.077 --> 1:16:06.147
Out loud.

1:16:12.119 --> 1:16:15.640
"Jordan, you are
African-American.

1:16:17.089 --> 1:16:19.609
No one can ever
take that away from you.

1:16:25.442 --> 1:16:27.030
You will be challenged

1:16:27.168 --> 1:16:30.378
because of your complexion
and the color of your eyes.

1:16:32.242 --> 1:16:35.729
But let your character and deeds
shine in everything you do.

1:16:37.144 --> 1:16:39.146
And never forget
where you came from."

1:16:39.284 --> 1:16:41.700
[]

1:16:43.564 --> 1:16:44.979
What's this?

1:16:46.705 --> 1:16:48.396
Your dad wrote it.

1:16:51.745 --> 1:16:53.816
He wrote everything in there
just for you.

1:16:55.438 --> 1:16:58.337
You're old enough now,
so I want you to read it.

1:17:00.167 --> 1:17:01.617
Every word.

1:17:25.675 --> 1:17:28.264
[ALL CHEER]

1:17:28.402 --> 1:17:29.852
Y'all know
it's not my birthday.

1:17:29.990 --> 1:17:31.750
Are y'all trying
to scam free dessert?

1:17:31.888 --> 1:17:33.787
Well, you wouldn't let us
celebrate last year,

1:17:33.925 --> 1:17:37.135
and I know how much you hate it
on the actual day, so...

1:17:37.273 --> 1:17:38.999
Make a wish.

1:17:40.690 --> 1:17:42.209
Whoa!

1:17:44.004 --> 1:17:45.902
You guys.Open mine first.

1:17:47.283 --> 1:17:48.387
Fine.

1:17:54.014 --> 1:17:56.913
[LAUGHING]

1:17:58.743 --> 1:18:01.262
Is this what I think it is?Mm-hm.

1:18:01.400 --> 1:18:03.126
If you won't let me
set you up on dates,

1:18:03.264 --> 1:18:04.749
you should at least
have some pleasure.

1:18:04.887 --> 1:18:06.129
I go on dates.

1:18:06.267 --> 1:18:07.613
Three dates
and a one-night stand

1:18:07.752 --> 1:18:10.409
in over a decade does not count.Mm-hm.

1:18:10.547 --> 1:18:12.411
Well, do I have to plug it in?Plug it in.

1:18:12.549 --> 1:18:15.207
And then work your way up
to the highest setting.

1:18:15.345 --> 1:18:17.071
Slowly.Not too slowly.

1:18:17.209 --> 1:18:18.417
You have one too?Oh, yeah.

1:18:18.555 --> 1:18:20.868
Yeah, we all do.Better than most boyfriends.

1:18:21.006 --> 1:18:22.145
No, I don't know about that,
boo-boo.

1:18:22.283 --> 1:18:23.560
Well, I do.

1:18:23.699 --> 1:18:25.079
It's better than my husband
half the time,

1:18:25.217 --> 1:18:26.287
I'll tell you that.

1:18:26.425 --> 1:18:28.600
Shit, wish I could
plug his ass in.

1:18:28.738 --> 1:18:30.498
Woof.Oh.

1:18:30.636 --> 1:18:32.259
[WHIRRING SLOWLY]

1:18:33.363 --> 1:18:35.711
[CLICKS, WHIRRING FASTER]

1:18:35.849 --> 1:18:37.436
Oh.

1:18:41.337 --> 1:18:43.028
Mom, what's that?

1:18:43.166 --> 1:18:44.927
Uh...

1:18:45.065 --> 1:18:49.310
It's a massager. For tension.
What's up?

1:18:49.448 --> 1:18:52.313
You think we could go see
my sister in Texas soon?

1:18:52.451 --> 1:18:54.315
Christina? Of course, baby.

1:18:54.453 --> 1:18:55.869
We should see her more.

1:18:56.007 --> 1:18:57.974
My dad said he wanted us
to get to know each other.

1:18:58.112 --> 1:19:01.253
Well, we can do that.
Come here.

1:19:08.847 --> 1:19:11.091
How come you barely ever
talk about him?

1:19:15.681 --> 1:19:17.925
Well, sometimes,
it hurts to remember.

1:19:19.651 --> 1:19:22.205
But I think about him
all the time.

1:19:22.343 --> 1:19:25.277
And I write about him too.
That makes me feel better.

1:19:25.415 --> 1:19:28.142
[]

1:19:28.280 --> 1:19:30.110
Why don't we have
any pictures of him?

1:19:30.248 --> 1:19:31.663
We do.

1:19:31.801 --> 1:19:34.148
Just that one on your desk
with the balloons.

1:19:37.255 --> 1:19:39.844
We'll put more up.

1:19:39.982 --> 1:19:43.917
With the folded flag, like
Nana and Grandpa King have?

1:19:44.055 --> 1:19:47.955
Well, the Army only gives those
to the family at the funeral.

1:19:50.268 --> 1:19:52.615
We're his family.We are.

1:19:55.307 --> 1:19:57.447
But technically, I'm not.

1:20:00.347 --> 1:20:02.798
Your father and I
never got married.

1:20:19.090 --> 1:20:22.403
My fellow citizens,
at this hour,

1:20:22.541 --> 1:20:25.337
American and coalition forces
are in the early stages

1:20:25.475 --> 1:20:28.030
of military operations
to disarm Iraq,

1:20:28.168 --> 1:20:29.583
to free its people,

1:20:29.721 --> 1:20:33.069
and to defend the world
from grave danger.

1:20:33.207 --> 1:20:35.520
On my orders, coalition forces

1:20:35.658 --> 1:20:39.179
have begun striking selected
targets of military importance

1:20:39.317 --> 1:20:42.423
to undermine Saddam Hussein's
ability to wage war.

1:20:42.561 --> 1:20:44.425
Hello?Hey.

1:20:44.563 --> 1:20:47.359
Hey, oh, my God, you scared me.

1:20:47.497 --> 1:20:50.915
I'm sorry. You okay?Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

1:20:51.053 --> 1:20:54.677
Oh, I got your painting.
It's beautiful. I love it.

1:20:54.815 --> 1:20:56.023
I'm glad you like it.

1:20:57.818 --> 1:21:00.752
Baby, uh, listen.Yeah?

1:21:03.893 --> 1:21:05.688
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

1:21:05.826 --> 1:21:07.000
What's wrong?

1:21:10.693 --> 1:21:13.316
Nothing. Nothing.What?

1:21:16.388 --> 1:21:18.632
I got my orders for Iraq.

1:21:26.571 --> 1:21:28.055
When do you deploy?

1:21:30.299 --> 1:21:31.783
I don't know.

1:21:33.302 --> 1:21:36.270
We transfer out
to Fort Irwin tomorrow.

1:21:36.408 --> 1:21:38.445
California? Yeah.

1:21:43.553 --> 1:21:45.245
When can I see you?

1:21:46.694 --> 1:21:48.248
That, I don't know.

1:22:15.447 --> 1:22:17.173
Charles, I need to talk to you.

1:22:17.311 --> 1:22:19.589
Call me back right away.
It's an emergency.

1:22:33.155 --> 1:22:35.053
[PHONE RINGING]

1:22:37.814 --> 1:22:39.506
Charles?What's wrong?

1:22:39.644 --> 1:22:40.748
Is that gunfire?

1:22:42.958 --> 1:22:44.821
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Yeah, I'm at the range.

1:22:44.960 --> 1:22:46.375
Is everything okay?

1:22:46.513 --> 1:22:48.480
I need to see you.
When can you come home?

1:22:48.618 --> 1:22:50.137
Are you okay?

1:22:50.275 --> 1:22:52.519
Yes, but I don't wanna talk
about it on the phone.

1:22:52.657 --> 1:22:54.555
Cease fire!Cease fire!

1:22:54.693 --> 1:22:56.281
Cease fire!Talk about what?

1:22:56.419 --> 1:22:58.835
Can you come this weekend?
Please?

1:22:58.974 --> 1:23:00.527
Baby, I can't just leave
like that.

1:23:00.665 --> 1:23:02.115
Okay, well, maybe
I can come and see you.

1:23:02.253 --> 1:23:04.807
Dana, tell me what's wrong.

1:23:06.429 --> 1:23:07.499
I wanna have a baby.

1:23:07.637 --> 1:23:09.225
What?

1:23:09.363 --> 1:23:11.089
I wanna get pregnant.

1:23:13.436 --> 1:23:14.334
Now?

1:23:14.472 --> 1:23:15.645
Yes. Now.

1:23:17.716 --> 1:23:20.547
Commence fire!Commence fire!

1:23:20.685 --> 1:23:21.997
Where's all this coming from?

1:23:22.135 --> 1:23:23.412
Because I wanna live life,

1:23:23.550 --> 1:23:25.241
and not just report on it.

1:23:25.379 --> 1:23:29.694
And I wanna live it with you
so please have a baby with me.

1:23:32.386 --> 1:23:33.905
Absolutely.

1:23:34.043 --> 1:23:37.736
Well, you don't wanna
take a second to think about it?

1:23:37.874 --> 1:23:39.359
I'm not asking you for a puppy.

1:23:39.497 --> 1:23:42.569
I don't need to think about it. Are you sure?

1:23:42.707 --> 1:23:44.916
You're the one who doesn't
sound too sure, Dana.

1:23:45.054 --> 1:23:47.781
I just don't understand how you
can make a decision so quickly.

1:23:47.919 --> 1:23:50.094
Because I made my mind up
a long time ago.

1:23:51.578 --> 1:23:53.131
Well, what if I can't
get pregnant?

1:23:53.269 --> 1:23:54.960
Marry me.What?

1:23:55.099 --> 1:23:56.893
Marry me.

1:23:58.654 --> 1:23:59.551
Okay.

1:24:00.207 --> 1:24:01.312
Okay?

1:24:01.450 --> 1:24:04.246
So is that a yes?

1:24:04.384 --> 1:24:08.043
Charles Monroe King, yes.
I will marry you.

1:24:08.181 --> 1:24:10.252
[WHOOPS]

1:24:10.390 --> 1:24:12.392
Cease fire! Cease fire!Cease fire!

1:24:14.911 --> 1:24:17.328
She said yes.Sir?

1:24:17.466 --> 1:24:19.123
I'm getting married!

1:24:19.261 --> 1:24:20.814
Hoo-ah!

1:24:20.952 --> 1:24:22.954
Hoo-ah!

1:24:23.092 --> 1:24:24.714
[CHUCKLES]
You heard that?

1:24:24.852 --> 1:24:27.062
[LAUGHS]

1:24:29.892 --> 1:24:31.928
- What is this?- A gift.

1:24:32.067 --> 1:24:33.516
We're going to see Dad.

1:24:39.281 --> 1:24:41.283
Jordan, I have work.
You have school.

1:24:41.421 --> 1:24:44.596
Mom. It's on a weekend.

1:24:44.734 --> 1:24:46.978
It's only Washington, D.C.,
it's not that far.

1:24:50.085 --> 1:24:52.259
Baby, give me and your auntie
a minute, please.

1:24:54.675 --> 1:24:55.607
Good luck.

1:25:01.165 --> 1:25:02.821
You have no right to do this,
Miriam.

1:25:02.959 --> 1:25:04.099
The hell I don't.

1:25:04.237 --> 1:25:06.653
He's my godson. I love him too.

1:25:06.791 --> 1:25:08.758
Who's paying for this?It's taken care of.

1:25:08.896 --> 1:25:11.002
So this was your idea?No. Jordan's.

1:25:11.140 --> 1:25:14.592
He e-mailed me.
He needs this trip.

1:25:14.730 --> 1:25:16.628
You both do.

1:25:18.975 --> 1:25:20.356
Hey.

1:25:20.494 --> 1:25:25.120
Listen, it's not like Charles
left you with nothing.

1:25:26.638 --> 1:25:29.124
We both know that little man
in there is special.

1:25:29.262 --> 1:25:30.849
And he needs you right now.

1:25:30.987 --> 1:25:32.989
[]

1:25:33.128 --> 1:25:34.991
He's not gonna be a kid
forever.

1:25:51.732 --> 1:25:54.149
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1:25:57.531 --> 1:26:00.707
PILOT [OVER PA]:
Sorry, folks. We're headed
for more choppy air.

